This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama in 2012, commemorating the 50th anniversary of the Vietnam War. In the proclamation, Obama honors the bravery and sacrifice of the more than 3 million servicemen and women who served in the war. He pays tribute to the 58,000 patriots who lost their lives and the heroes who suffered as prisoners of war. He also pledges to continue efforts to bring home the more than 1,600 service members who are still missing. The proclamation establishes a 13-year program to honor and thank the Vietnam War veterans, and calls upon federal, state, and local officials to hold appropriate programs and ceremonies to honor those who served. The proclamation is signed by Barack Obama on May 25, 2012.